Class CopyOfCongruenceAnalysisAAWithBinariesPruningSimulationFilteringCDFs

extends java.lang.Object

Author:
Joe Parker A Simple congruence analysis to compare the SSLS values of an AA dataset on two input trees and a de novo RAxML tree. Assumes the working directory has no existing RAxML runs with the same name (runID and alignment file name would be enough to screw it). NEW for this revision (0.0.1 r80): Data is now EXPLICITLY filtered for missing taxa (gaps) using the AlignedSequenceRepresentation.filterForMissingData(int filter, boolean useFactor) method. This method either removes: [useFactor = true]: any sites with a proportion of gaps > (filter/100); or [useFactor - false]: any sites with COUNT of gaps > filter useFactor = true is probably safer as there's no chance of setting filter < numTaxa (which would cause it to throw an exception). The only downside is that is harder to interpret (slightly) Also note that this means the PamlParameter cleandata should probably be set to cleandata=0 for most purposes.
